This Tundra program seems to correctly handle logic, however there is a syn
syntax issue in the if-else statement that results in it not behaving as ex
expected. The problem lies within the 'score' field of the user record (rep
(report.user.score), which should be compared against the passMark value st
stored inside report object. 

Here is the corrected Tundra code:

```tundra
val report = {
  user: {
    name: "Ada",
    score: 68
  },
  passMark: 70
};

if (report.user.score > report.passMark) {
  print("review");
} else {
  print("pass");
}
```

This program will compare the user's score with the passing mark and it sho
should give expected output as "review" since, the score of the user (68) i
is greater than the pass mark (70). It won't run into any runtime errors or
or observe a failure.
